race.comment: QUEEN TAVANE (9) is still a maiden but doing enough to suggest she can win this. Worked home okay without threatening last start in a Warwick Farm maiden over the mile. Crying out for this trip. Like the engagement of Jeff Penza who will give her every chance. THINK OF ONE (7) is a 15-start maiden who worked home evenly to finish fifth over 1600m at Kembla recently. Cherry ripe now and should cope with his first try beyond 1800m. THE BENTLEY (6) stepped up in distance and improved sharply last start at the second run of the campaign. On trial at 2000m but still warrants consideration. KITSILANO (5) filled a minor placing at his only run over this course and distance. Strong effort at this track last time - one for the exotics. ZOUGO BOSS (8) isn't going well but in a race thin on chances a top four finish is on the cards.
